sentence: Fastenal Company ( FAST ) will begin trading ex-dividend on July 23, 2014.
A cash dividend payment of $0.25 per share is scheduled to be paid on August 22, 2014.
Shareholders who purchased FAST stock prior to the ex-dividend date are eligible for the cash dividend payment.
This marks the 5th quarter that FAST has paid the same dividend.
At the current stock price of $45, the dividend yield is 2.22%.
The previous trading day's last sale of FAST was $45, representing a -13.81% decrease from the 52 week high of $52.21 and a 5.93% increase over the 52 week low of $42.48.
FAST is a part of the Consumer Services sector, which includes companies such as Home Depot, Inc. ( HD ) and Lowe's Companies, Inc. ( LOW ).
FAST's current earnings per share, an indicator of a company's profitability, is $1.55.
Zacks Investment Research reports FAST's forecasted earnings growth in 2014 as 10.07%, compared to an industry average of 8.2%.
For more information on the declaration, record and payment dates, visit the FAST Dividend History page.
